caption: Constantly good food, well presented, friendly atmosphere, variety choices, well priced generous portions and always generous when asked to donate to organizations. A very nice "go to spot"
Mim’s is my go to restaurant during the Pandemic. They are following all of the COVID protocols and I feel very safe.  The food is delicious as it has always been.
The food is always excellent. When we eat in the restaurant the service is always excellent as well. The pick up service is made very easy and smooth to handle
Waiter was excellent
This is our 2nd and the drinks and the atmosphere doesn't disappoint.  We will be back. The Chinese chicken salad was very good and the dessert was delicious.
Excellent service and super food for all of the family! Brought friends in this past Saturday night...ALL excellent...Salmon on vegetable saiad...WOW!...
The food is always on point .  The service and staff are professional and prompt.
Excellent food at a very reasonable price

Just ate here today. Nice atmosphere BUT they took 45 min to bring our food and when our bill came we saw that they charge $4 for each soda. They also added 20% automatic tip for large parties, yet it was only my husband and I and our 4 sons (all kids). Between those 2 things our bill went up by $50. That was a turnoff. I want to tip what I want to tip according to the service received. And I also don't want to pay $4 for a water down soda. The food... some dishes were better than others, some of the food was cold, another was bland. Maybe they forgot to season it.
Took my Mom to Mim’s for lunch. We had a wonderful meal, great service.

My children and I loved the food. I enjoyed my tuna well done with their dips. We loved the service and menu. The lighting and decor is nice and cozy. Come here to eat and come hungry. Also, you may come nicely dressed.

We have always enjoyed eating and taking out from Mim's in Roslyn.  When it first opened we were very happy since we had heard good things about their restaurant in Syosset.  On short notice we were able to eat at Mim's on New Year's eve several years ago and had a delicious affordable meal.  Of special note are their main dish salads, their fantastic pasta dishes, and the scrumptious desserts.  The servers are great and it's a nice comfortable place where you can have a conversation with friends. Don't miss a meal there!  And the prices are very reasonable. And if you are like us, afraid to go out due to CoVid, the takeout options are a super deal and the food is just as good as inside. We look forward to returning to the restaurant when it's safe.
We love this place!  Fresh,  delicious food, wonderful staff, beautiful ambiance, always our first choice!

We have been dining at Mims for years. The food is always wonderful and the staff is consistently great. During COVID, we have pretty much switched to take out for regular dinners as well as some of the holiday menus. Everyone is so accommodating and pick up is a breeze. So important to support great small business like this, especially when the food and service enhance our quality of life!
Amazing Stuff provided excellent service. Super satisfied . food was yummy. cozy place. velvet parking is the plus.
Process beginning to end was flawless!
We had a great experience service and food was good We had to leave I didn't get my soup that was included in my meal I always enjoy my visit

My last  visit to Mim’s was in a party of ten. They sat us in a pretty section  where we were comfortable and everyone could hear each other. Felt like we were in a home! Food was tasty and fun and filling. Loved it! Everyone on their staff was super friendly. Will return again soon. Jay P.

My all time favorite and go to places to eat are Mims and Mill Creek Tavern. Food is always on point, tastes delicious and great atmosphere. Both are great to go with family and equally fun for date night. Spring rolls are an all time classic and a must have every time I go. I highly recommend, it will not disappoint!
Fantastic food and great service!
Mims is the best restaurant around. Great food service and lots of great specials .I have been going  there  for years and it continues to shine
our server was excellent. wine selection was great. food came out pretty quickly :)
Absolutely incredibly Cuban sandwich!
Food, service, atmosphere and price cannot be beat.
Excellent food and drinks.

Last week was our first time we visited this fine restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the excellent service, with the high quality  cuisine and fine drinks and with the friendly charge. We will definitely go back there soon.
Delicious Cuban sandwich.  Try it, you'll have about it, too.  Friendly, happy servers.  Go there, great atmosphere, too.

Horrible juice. The kids won’t even drink this. When asked they said it’s Tropicana. Don’t know where they brought this from. When the bill came noticed that they didn’t include the orange juice. Good.  Here is the twist. Had ordered Hennessy for adults and it didn’t taste like Henny. So told them it’s not Hennny. Just wanted to make sure so I went to the bar and asked for another Hennessy. The bartender replied ok and vanished from the bar . Waited patiently for 3+ min and she came back and said she checked the basement and couldn’t find any more Hennessy. I said THANK YOU. Then came the receipt with added TIP wrote down by the waitress in addition to the service charge they already charged. I understand the service charge, Because we were total 11 ppl but I never see an employee fill out the tip by themselves. Seriously??? First she said get the calculator and next second she realized she was wrong. Then comes the usual apology and she said this was the first time.  I wanted to tip them extra because of the pandemic, but when asked why did she do that she said they just started doing this today. Hearing that I thanked them saying I am going to do this review and will never come here again.  The owner did reply as usual. He said they got a new system. I don’t mind. But if the employees are not trained with the new system they shouldn’t write down the tip by themselves. Also to the owner it wasn’t henny you guys gave us.
Mims has been a family staple for years. Friendly staff and great food. All anyone needs when going out for dinner.
Very nice atmosphere and the service was great.  We enjoyed a great meal with great wine. They have vellay parking, but parking is easy to find nearby as well.
My new spot in Roslyn! No judging & food is on point!
Mims Restaurant never disappoints. The food is consistently delicious - the staff is always attentive and friendly. Highly recommend this delicious spot!
Good food. competent staff.
The food is regularly well prepared and delightful, workers hands out awesome service. I like how clean it is and ambience. I highly recommend this place.

A very nice space with lots of room. Excellent service and good food.  My friend and I enjoyed the brussel spouts appetizer as well as our Cobb Salads.  The special cocktail that we had was really tasty! We had quite a few Kentucky Ciders!  Our server Kierre was outstanding.  She was so attentive to us and truly excellent at her job!  Mim's is a good spot for any occasion.  I'll be back for sure!
Great atmosphere and great food
The best food and service you would ever want! Our family would very highly recommend Mim’s.
You can't go wrong when the pandemic is over and you could even eat  inside   service is spectacular. Right now pick up  is fantastic because the the food is great
Great food, cozy environment for gathering with friends. Always consistently excellent
Had a wonderful dinner, the staff was very accommodating and the food was excellent.
Delicious food and great service!
Very nice food here.
Great place and food
Everyone was nice and helpful. Made our first dinner at mim's since the pandemic worth the trip.

The food was excellent and the service was great. Can’t wait to go back again! Jimmy the manager is always friendly and makes sure all the food comes out correctly. We also felt very Covid safe there.
Always good 👍.  Nice night to eat outside in Mims tent.
Always a great group of people to be around
AMAZING FOOD GREAT SERVICE!
The food was incredible everything was fresh & delicious ,  great service and really  friendly atmosphere.
love their menu. service was good. food was great. outdoor dining was well organized. left my card there by accident and they gave me no problems picking it up. would definitely go back.
Great food. Well prepared very tasty. Great take out service too. Definitely will make this a regular place to go to.
Ask for the pan seared sea scallops and Lemon Sole Oregon delicious:) I recommend it
Food was good, service good as well
Dined at Mim's with family on Sunday night.. It was a really nice dinner.. Almost pre=covid.. Enjoyed by all. Thank you,Mims

Was there for dinner last on 10/10. The tent Set up allowed for more than adequate social distancing. As usual the service was attentive even when my grandson broke a water glass. Food preparation was impeccable and a good time was had by all

We LOVE Mims! It has been our go to place that never disappoints. The location is unbeatable, we meet friends from Manhattan, Westchester, the south shore & out east here. It is convenient to all. The menu is varied so even our pickiest of friends or kids are pleased. While we have been quarantined we enjoyed their curb side take-out. I cannot say enough, the staff always tries to please, the chef is accommodating. I’ve been to several parties as well. The space makes for a wonderful flow, the food was beautifully presented and delicious!!!
Love Mims! Great food and amazing service!!!

This spot is my preferred one. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very professional and the cooking they place on your table is so yummy. I would always prefer to have a nice dinner in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.
I ave been a patron of Mim’s restaurant for years!  The food is great , along with the atmosphere, as well as a wonderful staff!
Outdoor dining! Perfect

Always great food and a very courteous staff.  Prices are very reasonable and there is a wonderful selection of beer wine and cocktails. Plenty of appetizers and main courses to choose from; their fajitas are awesome!  The portions are quite ample but save room for dessert.

Mim’s is one of our favorite places to enjoy. Having a delicious meal, party & fundraisers, we have always been happy with their menu & service. We have been going for many years. The managers are hands on & always available. It’s the “go to” place.

The Food is always amazing. Everyone that works there so far has made it a nice experience expect their host. We felt unwelcome and like the host didn’t care to seat. Normally I don’t complain but the rest of the staff are always awesome and the one reason I don’t turn away is because of them. I don’t want to see this place to lose customers over a unhappy host other I highly recommend this place because their food is on point.

I celebrated my PhD yesterday in this great restaurant. happy to tell that we enjoyed a awesome evening and the venue was no doubt one of the reasons for that outstanding event. The team  collaborated in a splendid manner, the meals were great and my guests were so  delighted. We shall no dout visit again for more events. Thank you very much.
Mim’s always provides good food, great service, and incredible pina coladas!  You can’t go wrong either taking out or dining at Mim’s
Excellent variety of food Cooked very well Great atmosphere Valet parking available  Great restaurant 👍👍👍
They offer an awesome range of delicious food. I enjoyed eating here. Employees are always very nice, prices are convenient and the spot is always kept clean.

Went to Mim's with my girlfriends for a holiday get together, we had a great time. We enjoyed the specialty cocktails. We also enjoyed the pretzel brie and the spinach dip for our apps. For dinner I had the sesame tuna it was great, my friends had the chicken with apples and the stuffed sole, they loved it. We ended with brownie sundae!!!  Service was excellent, Debbie was our server. We will be back for our next gathering.
Excellent eating experience.. from walking in the door and being greeted by employee and very Safe Environment. Meal was served hot and excellent taste. Server was very friendly and helpful.
Service a little slow but the food was good.....
I have been eating here for years. The food is always wonderful, the portions are generous and the staff is welcoming. Great for a date or out with the family.

We always have a great meal either at Mim's or from Mim's.  Service is wonderful.  Food is delicious and consistent.  My husband loves the Ciabatta chicken sandwich.  I love the Plank Salmon and crispy brussel sprouts.

Started off at the bar for a cocktail, eric was great.  moved over to a table, we had a reservation and were sat immediately upon request.  The food was great and service was fantastic.  Seems obvious why the Mims name has been around for so long.  Not only would I go back, but I plan too.
Great food and excellent service!

Always have had a good experience at MIMs. Prices are reasonable food is always high quality. My kids did our 40th wedding anniversary surprise party there l, not even knowing it’s our favorite place and they did an amazing job Highly recommend!

you had the food delivered to the house and it was perfect.  we had dinner for six and I could find nothing to fault.   food was hot, tasty and eye appealing.   thanks for a great Wednesday night dinner
The food is good and nice serving size. The staff is attentive and friendly. Good place to go for a family dinner.
Love Mim's restaurant!  The food is always great and the wait staff is wonderful.

Always consistently delicious food!  Glad to see they are doing Curbside Take Out now. I would miss not being able to have Mim's as an option in our dinner rotation!  We had them cater our New Year's party and everyone wanted to know where the food came from. Fresh and delicious.

I'm in love with this place, the food, the service and the atmosphere is all amazing.  I tell all my friends about the wonderful experiences I've had every time I eat at MIM's.  This place is a MUST try.
Great restaurant. Food is delicious. They have also created a wonderful outdoor space for the pandemic.

I have had the chance to dine at both locations mill creek tavern in Bayville and Mims Roslyn several times it is always my first choice when going out to eat for my family and I the menu is awesome contemporary American with a lot of comfort food the service is always on point and love the ambiance in both restaurants can’t wait to get back and dine again with you guys thanks for all the memories!!!
Mim’s is an authentic Italian restaurant with great food and atmosphere. The owner and his staff are warm and welcoming! It’s our go to for a night out!
Excellent food and wonderful service. Highly recommended

Rich and his team are absolutely amazing to work with! The food is beyond incredible, everything is made with the finest ingredients, and his staff is personable, friendly and professional. We've had numerous events catered from here and our guests are always calling us the next day to rave about the food! We love the food and team so much that we just booked them to cater our wedding!
Great restaurant for family, dates, and celebrations.  The menu has something for everyone.  The food never disappoints.  They have been wonderful during the Pandemic.
Great food excellent service.
Food tasted great and authentic. Service was excellent.
Great place. Picked up burgers which were awesome. Also ate out doors and enjoyed it so much. Wait staff is super. Food is always great
Outstanding restaurant! Loved the food and the atmosphere and staff are top-notch. Can't wait to go again.
Another delicious meal!  Do yourself a favor and try those Brussel Sprouts!!!
Easy parking, diverse menu, food is well prepared and service is attentive.  We enjoy going to Mim’s!
Food, service and ambiance was excellent. Both pre and post pandemic always enjoy Mims!
Such a Fantastic place, there’s something for everyone and it’s all done with love.  Year after year it never disappoints!!!!
We have been going to Mim's for years Great options, friendly staff and good food!
Food is excellent.
I have been here several times!! I absolutely love the food there. The never ever disappoint!! There is never really a wait either..
alot of money for average food
Great food! Wonderful staff! Always accommodating. My favorite go-to restaurant.
Mim's is always my go to comfort food restaurant. In times like today, it is even more of that special place.
Excellent meal
Mim’s is an exceptional dinning experience.  The staff, menu and food are top notch.  I would highly recommend this restaurant.  5 stars.
Great Happy Hour with sizable delicious appetizers. Dinner Specials are well portioned and creative. Lively atmosphere and music events. Parking lot is a plus as well.
Food is always good.  Nice neighborhood restaurant.
Consistantly wonderful! A terrific variety of choices. Everything so delicious i have a hard time trying something different. Cozy atmosphere. I cant go enough! GC gal

You’re always guaranteed a good meal here. I have been even here for years and have never been disappointed. The service is attentive but not overbearing it is a nice atmosphere the menu is varies and there’s always something on everybody. Excellent value for your dollar
Food was exactly as ordered & ready for pick up when we arrived. All very good & good value!
Had a fantastic experience here with my girlfriend. The food came fast and the customer service is just great. Prices are convenient.
Delicious food and great service every time! It's one of my "go to" restaurants! I would definitely recommend you giving them a try!
Went here for a business lunch. It was delicious!
I love Mim’s! The service is always good, and the  food never disappoints. Mims is great to meet friends, for date night , and for family celebrations. Definitely recommend it!
Mims is one of our favorite restaurants on the island! The food is consistently delicious. We’re missing the beautiful atmosphere of dining in but love that they’re open for curbside.
Great Food and Great service. I highly recommend it

I’d like to consider myself a regular at Mim’s as it’s one of our favorites, but I live in Wantagh so it is not so easy to just hop on over for a dinner with the kids. We go a few times a year and love it every time. Great variety and never disappointed. When I found myself in the Roslyn area last week, I decided to order takeout from their Family Deals. Figured it wouldn’t be as good as when we dine in but still a nice change from our normal takeout. I was wrong!!  The portions were great (especially for the price) and everything was packaged well. Still hot when I got home 20 minutes later. Food quality seems to be the same as always. I, of course,didn’t have much interaction with the staff but it was ready exactly when I asked for it. Can’t ask for more. Thanks for staying open!  (I also noticed on their website they offer a big discount to front line health care workers.  Next time I’ll send my wife who works at NUMC. I’ll save some money and get great food from a local business.)
My go to place when I am on Long Island! Mims is the best! Amazing Food, friendly and accommodating staff. I always leave happy and stuffed! I can't say enough good things about them! # 1 in my book!
Never disappointed!

Fantastic food and even better service! Mim's is a godsend during these tough times. They are offering a full menu including FAMILY MEALS TO-GO (buffalo spring rolls and grilled skirt steak are AMAZING!!) plus beer, wine and cocktails to-go. The family meals can easily serve 4 people and they offer additional appetizers and entrees if you are feeding more than that. You can place an order by calling directly or using uber eats/doordash. They are also offering no-contact curbside pickup!
Food is always on point, staff is always friendly and knowledgeable. The curbside pick up has been a lifesaver for me during this time. Thanks MIMS and staff!! Keep up the good work and great food!

Absolutely love this place and have loved it ever since it opened many years ago.  It's always my first choice.  Food is delicious and very accommodating.  Staff is the best!  During these times, the owner Rich has opened for curbside pickup and it is amazing!!!!
Got the family meal and it was soo good! The food was well prepared and delicious. Nice to have a meal like that during these hard times!

The Family meal deal is awesome! Everything we had from appetizer to dessert was just as good as it would be if we ate it there! (Remember those days! Lol) The best part- I didn’t have to cook, clean up was fast and I had leftovers for the next day! The food was ready when they said, pick up was easy (thanks Jimmy!) and packaged well. And you can’t beat the price either! We’ll be ordering again!

It is my pleasure to support Mim's during these challenging times.  Rich and his establishment have done so much for the community over the years and it is good to be there for him and his staff as they try to support their families as well.  Their food has been just as delicious as to go as it is for sit down.  I do miss the atmosphere inside as it is cozy and fun.  My go to is always the meatloaf and the Banana Betty, so yummy!  thanks again for all you do and can't wait to see you all soon!
Friendly service, good food, great deserts- never disappointed.
Great food, friendly
I eat here a lot since I work close by. I have to say the service is always fantastic and they keep the spot well kept regularly. Rates are fair and they serve large portions.
Food delicious. Great staff!  Wonderful Happy hour! Always accommodating!
Great food!  Valet parking or watch the street signs.

This restaurant is my number one place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. when  I I need a fair dinner, this is the place that comes right away to my mind. superb and   food and a rich cuisine.well mannered staff, and agreeable vibes. Also, the cost is fair. I praise this spot with pleasure.
Mim's is always SPOT ON!  An excellent food and service experience. Every time!!

Oh MY gosh, I can’t say enough nice things about how great it was to work with Mim’s!! I had a gender reveal party at my home this past weekend & had them do trays of food for 40. We picked it all up ourselves & set up on our own sterno heated tray holders to serve. We had the sautéed chicken with mozzarella & tomatoes, mustard grilled salmon & marinated steak for entrees. Mac & cheese was the best anyone had ever had from a restaurant. Mixed veggies were fabulous & caesar salad was great too. They included rolls.  The catering manager Jimmy made it all so easy. Chef put in his recommendations on food amounts which were PERFECT-barely any leftovers which made us a little sad haha! You really can’t beat $600 for a REALLY nice catered dinner for 40 people. A HUGE thank you to the entire Mim’s team for impressing the hell out of me, my husband & our entire family. The food absolutely made the party.  By the way, it’s a girl!!
Good food at reasonable prices.  Wait staff is excellent.
Food and costumer service is great, also reasonable prices.

This place is always the spot to go for a great drink, great food and great atmosphere. You can either park your self or have valet parking. Once you walk in the bar and small eating area is to the right and the main dining area is straight I front if you co tonite walking. I have had the pleasure to dine and both areas and seriously the experience was great. There is a wide selection of food and drinks and they have great deals and promotions. The bathrooms are always clean. Definitely a place to check out over and over and over again:) Oh btw the bartender are great!!!!
Mims always is top notch. Food,  service and management are consistently excellent.
Great place to share a special moments with family, friends, meetings. And the food was great. Also the person that attended us, very polite and always pending about us
Mims is always a go to for my wife and I.  We gone there for date night, birthdays, anniversary' and we always have an enjoyable time.
Been going for years. Really good.
I had a superb  in this restaurant. We enjoyed the nice ambience and the menu. The waiters were very affable. I am glad we ultimately decided to visit here.
Christmas dinner good times

Was there Sat Jan 25 with a few couples and We love this place - great variety and friendly staff - but I have to leave this review with a minor complaint in the grand scheme of life   The food needs to be served more quickly so the temperature is hot not warm when you get your food i notice other restaurants have food runners who ONLY serve food (back and forth from kitchen to tables) and do nothing else - just a thought
The service , the food was excellent.another great Birthday dinner with family. Our waitress was the best. Wish I knew her name
Every time I visit this place I am exceedingly happy. They hold their high  level service and the highest level of dishes  they serve. Always the best!

Nice looking place but not all are welcome here according to how I was treated by the hostess. I came in to pick up an online order ahead of two groups. The hostess overlooked me by greeting and attending to the group behind me. I graciously stepped out of their way and allowed them to be pass to be seated. The hostess again greeted the next group behind me to which I interrupted her this time and told her that I too was waiting to be helped. She acted surprise as if she was seeing me for the first time. This was a racial related incident for sure☹.  Thanks for your response below, but it took you two months to knowledgeable and respond to my concern whereas, you responded immediately to other reviews. I have been in your restaurant at least six times and have always been greeted and picked up orders at the reception desk, NEVER at the bar. I have never been allowed pass the reception area in the front. I will say that on the above visit was the first time I experienced such distasteful treatment,  so I'll call it an isolated or one-off incident. As for diverse and multicultural....never seen it....only the valet attendant. I will say though that your food smells delicious...too bad I'll never taste it.

I had a surprise birthday dinner and as usual the dinner and staff were excellent.  No complaints except that a cake was made by a friend and there was a charge to plate it.  It would have been more appropriate to just give a slice to everyone who wanted it.  We will come back nevertheless as we love Mim’s and easy for all to get there.
Great food, plentiful menu, good specials,friendly efficient wait staff.
Used door dash and ordered Chinese chicken salad.  Requested no peanuts as I am not allowed to eat nuts.  It was full of peanuts.  Think I was given xtra nuts.

Very nice Italian restaurant very well located.  The food is consistently good and is not too exorbitant.   They run special for dinner that offer real value for the money.  The bar is really nice and  they seem to have a crowd of regulars for Happy Hour every night.  Service is generally superior and it never disappoints.

This is a 4 1/2 stars.....great food.......excellent wait staff.......enjoy the fact that we are not rushed from the table; we meet friends from Brooklyn, we each travel a nice distance, and we catch up, so a fine meal with time to enjoy friendship is a big plus....
Good food, friendly service and the price is right. Give it a try you will not be disappointed.

Great place to meet up with friends and enjoy a fabulous meal.  Or sit at the bar and enjoy discounted appys that are just as delicious. Tommy is welcoming and manages the bar no matter how busy it gets and the hand off at end of shift is seamless. Servers are well versed on their menu and offer suggestions.  The restsurant is clean with nice appointments and cozy.  Never disappointed.
Great food, atmosphere was awesome and the bartender is amazing!

By far my favorite and the best restaurant and place to go for a fabulous meal and time out.  Drinks, food and staff don’t get any better. I have been coming to Mims for a very long time and am never disappointed. My best times and meals are here. Best cosmos, bread, hummus , salad, burata, lemon sole oreganata, fish , chicken, steak prepared any and all ways.. desserts that are to die for.. and the list goes on.  People go out to eat for a good meal. Which you will absolutely have:get  at Mim's.. but one gets so much more here. The most incredible staff and people are all under one roof. No doubt all the servers are great, but Angela is my personal favorite. She’s Amazing..And then some!  Last but not least . A big shout out and Thank  you to Jimmy. Mim’s is what is is  because of  him! Jimmy goes above and beyond to make sure Everyone is happy and all  their needs and wants are met.. He is truly so rare, terrific  snd special. How lucky Mims and all of us are to have him!!  Will be back soon! And if  you’re reading this review and stressing where to go.. look no further.. Go to Mim’s. You won’t be disappointed!  This posting was done a while ago. Well I’m happy to say some things don’t change. Repeat to Everything in my previous review  Mims is still THE BEST! Still my favorite place to come to dine, drink, and have the BEST time, meal and drinks. Still the best staff ever... and still especially Jimmy and Angela. I love you both . When they made you they broke the mole. You truly are the best in every way!! Mims, every diner, I, and this world..are so lucky to have you in it! Tommy, Sean and Ivan.. You all make great drinks too!🍷🍷🍷🍸🍸🍸  See you all Friday!😊🤗.. Can’t wait!!  And to everyone reading this review.. a very picky diner is telling you to come to Mims if you want the best of everything  under one roof!!
The drink list was very good great selection to choose from. The food selection was great and the service was excellent will return.
Tommy the bartender is terrific..nice neighborhood rest good food
Greatest
This was the first time we ate there, the menu was excellent with many choices, the atmosphere was very nice. The staff was great and very friendly.
Great food easy app loved it will use it again
Delicious burger
Consistently good food and professional, friendly staff!
Great tasting food
Awesome restaurant, service and ambience. Food was ok to the most part. Salads were good but way too green and lettucey, wings were good but very hot, fish tacos were flavorless.
Everything was ok. Not good just another meal.
Food was great no matter what we each choice. Service was attentive without being annoying. Always good!!

Went there on a company lunch and really enjoyed the food.  One of the server was a little rude but who cares maybe she was having a bad day.  Hope her day got better.  The food was really delicious. Planning to go back soon with my husband. Oh cant forget the dessert.. I think I got sugar drunk lol but it was goooodddd.
Food was average but I liked the vibe.
Service is great.
Great happy hour.
Our go to place for over 20 yrs.  Great food and service.  We love Jimmy and Angela!
Outstanding food and great service. Always enjoy a visit to Mim’s.
Very delicious food. Especially loved the burgers and fries would recommend to anyone near the area.
I often think that Mim's exists just for people to meet between Queens and Long Island.  No matter what you order, the food is just OK.  Nothing special.  Nothing outstanding.  Just OK.
Always does their best with my orders there!

From the moment  you step in this place  the personel give you an excellent feeling. Very friendly team, it is a nice place to  pass time with buddies or with your date. tasty  cooking, qualified  chef, good  pay and nice  service. Highly recommended.

I meet with friends this place quite a bit! This is my favorite restaurant to eat.  I visit this spot many times. The food is excellent, the team is welcoming and the rates are reasonable. I enjoy being in this restaurant to have a nice supper.

Bartender was also my waiter for a quick lunch. Had me sit in a booth so he was running. Service &  quality was excellent. Not used to valet parking for lunch. Great place. Will stop again when on business.

From the first moment  you step in that place  the waiters give you a pleasant feeling. Very friendly hosts, it is a good restaurant to hang out with your friends or with your date. enjoyable  cuisine, professional  chef de cuisine, modest  pay and courteous  service. Highly recommended.
Good food.  Service was a bit slow for a business lunch.
Exceptional food, very friendly staff, constantly  awesome ambience. They charge fair prices and the food quality is good. Keep up the good work.
Consistently good
The food and service were above our expectations. We surely liked the vibes of this place. First-rate spot to take the family out for lunch.

Conveniently located on Roslyn Road, less than a mile off the major parkways is Mim's, a charming, cozy restaurant offering the best in service and food. There is a good-sized bar with dining so you can watch the latest sporting event and several dining areas, including big comfy booths too. Mim's hosts themed dining nights as well as fun events like Psychic Nights and Murder Mystery Dinners.  The event nights are usually priced-fixed with a set menu, offering you several quality choices in appetizers, main courses, and dessert. When we dine here on other nights we have also enjoyed their barbeque special as Southern cooking with Mac n Cheese and ribs, don't get any better according to our son, a big fan of everything bbq. I always enjoy their steaks, and on several lucky nights, their dinner special has been a delicious lamb selection. I always go for their Brussel Sprouts, and you won't be disappointed either especially if you like them roasted crispy. For dessert, they have a make your own smores, always a favorite family item or their cheesecake and pies are outstanding. Another comfort here is both a pleasant and accommodating staff as well as a great atmosphere. No matter the crowd Mim's draws and serves; the valet takes your car, the server promptly starts your drink order and kitchen turn around time is appropriately spaced between courses even on event nights. I have also picked up restaurant gift cards here for my friends, and they also have an excellent lunch menu too!  While I am not psychic, I can predict a great meal and an enjoyable night awaits you at Mim's!

We went to Mim's after visiting Tilles Center with my daughter and her family, including 2 children, ages 6 and 10.  The reviews were outstanding so I expected a pleasant, trouble free evening of good food, pleasant service and comfortable surroundings.  The best I can say is almost.      While the service was mostly attentive and the food was very good for many, others were less than satisfied.  4 adults had soup or salad and an entree and the children had pasta and chicken parm that they loved.  The biggest issue was that the Chicken pot pie crust was charred and, even though it was very hot, the potatoes were under cooked, a real issue for my wife who is severely allergic to under cooked potatoes. I should have suspected an issue when our entrees were taking a unusual amount of time.  The waitress did come by to acknowledged that they were taking long and that she would check why.  My guess is they were waiting for the pot pie as the sides for the others were at best warm and they forgot shrimp add on. Finally, we were just unlucky to be seated next to a party of eight that were extremely loud but that is more a comment about our culture that the restaurant. Overall it was not a bad experience. The restaurant did not charge for the pot pie and the shrimp they originally forgot to add to the pasta primavera.  We had drinks and a bottle of wine and except for pot pie and warm sides enjoyed the rest of the entrees.  We will give Mim's another try and hopefully they will live up to their reviews at that time.

I came into this Restaurant looking for a server job. I was scheduled for an interview, handed in my resume the same day and was told to come in for training.  I came in for my first day of training on a Wednesday and everything went well. Jimmy the manager had told me to return on Thursday and Friday at 4pm. I showed up on Thursday and at the end of my shift I was reminded to come back the next day. On Friday at 3:55pm Jimmy called me not to come in and mentioned how he could not accommodate me in the schedule. Meanwhile I was outside the parking lot, after making the 45 minute commute through rush hour to get there. I called back to ask about pay for the shifts I have completed.  I was put on hold for 10 minutes and was told by Trisha that Jimmy “stepped out”.  I left a message with Trisha and never received a call back. I proceeded to call back two more times on different days. As soon as I mentioned who I was and who I wanted to speak to, I would get the run around “Jimmy is not here” or “Jimmy stepped out”.  Not only did I waste my time and energy, I wasted my money on a $60 uniform that I cannot return because It was used for the two days of training. Mims is the most unprofessional place I’ve ever came across.  I had to contact the Department of Labor due to the irresponsibility of a manager. I do not encourage anybody to apply here. Your time and money will be wasted.  I also don’t encourage costumers to eat at an establishment who mistreats their employees. If I could give this restaurant 0 stars or even negative stars, I would.

My family and I ate a late lunch (3 pm) here on the way home. The available parking was limited, the place is kind of small. The decor on the inside is very nice, subdued and gives an elegant feel without being extravagant. I ordered the meatloaf and my wife had the sauteed chicken. Both dishes were very good. The potatoes were excellent, with a crispy skin (but not dry!) and soft interior. For dessert I had the chocolate mousse cake with oreo crumb topping. By this point I was full so I had a couple of spoonfuls of cake and it tasted good. Full disclosure I'm very picky about desserts. My son finished my cake in about two minutes, so he highly recommends it. The service was good but I would expect the server to be able to pay close attention to a table in a mostly empty restaurant on a  Thursday afternoon. Overall I liked Mim's and i would definitely eat there again if I am in the area.

This place has a diverse selection of appetizers and entrees.  I ordered the skirt steak over pasta.  The steak was perfect as far as flavor and texture.  The pasta was a little under salted.  The spinach and artichoke dip was nice.  The tuna tartare could probably use a little revision.  It just didn't feel right with the mango salsa.  I had the Tuesday margarita special.  $7 for a rita, and I believe it was top shelf.  Overall, the food did not disappoint, and the service was excellent.  Our server checked on us many times.  I will definitely come back and explore the menu some more.

Lunch spot

Exceptional service and atmosphere as well as good food. My wife and I had a drink before dinner at the bar.  Tommy the bartender was engaging as well as other people at the bar. For dinner, my wife had a buffalo chicken spring roll and I had a wedge salad (Iceberg lettuce, applewood bacon, red onions, cherry tomatoes, bleu cheese dressing).  Both were very good. For dinner, my wife had the sesame crusted tuna.  I had a marinated skirt steak and a baked potato with the works.  Again, both were very good as well as their cheesecake and oreo moose pie. Neil our server was exceptional.  He knew the menu and his recommendations were spot on.  I highly recommend and we will be back.
